 Sorry, we do not handle proxies in our Web server, so that would
 indeed be the source of the error.  It's only meant to be a
 documentation browser, not a general-purpose Web browser (-:.  The
 simplest thing to do when you encounter a missing documentation bundle 
 in Help Desk is to use your regular browser to download the .plt
 file.  Then go Help Desk's "Open URL", click on "Browse", and choose
 the downloaded .plt file.  Help Desk will install it for you.
 
 'shriram

